           =2 
           =2 // The following flags may be set in the global variable uip_flags
           =2 // before calling the application callback. The UIP_ACKDATA and
           =2 // UIP_NEWDATA flags may both be set at the same time, whereas the
           =2 // others are mutualy exclusive. Note that these flags should *NOT* be
           =2 // accessed directly, but through the uIP functions/macros.
